1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on accelerating deep neural network execution on mobile devices for image classification tasks using the ImageNet dataset. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel acceleration framework for deep neural networks and uses layer-wise fine-tuning to avoid accuracy loss. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with optimizing deep neural networks for real-time processing on mobile devices, which is a key application area of AI. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a method for optimizing the execution of deep neural networks, which is a key area of research in neural computing. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with optimizing deep neural networks for image classification tasks, which is a key application area of multimedia.
